node.title: The ‘Double Whammy’ That Is Slowing New York City’s Job Growth
node.description: The city has regained fewer than 6 of every 10 jobs it lost since the pandemic began, while the nation as a whole has regained more than 90 percent of lost jobs.

node.title: Joe Biden Urged by Democrats to Keep Promise and Cancel Student Debt

node.title: Sandra Lindsay reflects on her vaccine, 1 year later: ‘I felt like it was my civic duty.’
node.description: “I look back now with a lot of pride, knowing that I did my part,” said Ms. Lindsay, the New York-area nurse who was the first person in the United States to get vaccinated outside a clinical trial.

node.title: 'Charitable' Teenage Boy Dies of Stroke After Catching COVID
